Commentary Text: Pretorius to Karthik, out Harshal Patel Run Out!! DK wants the strike and that's why he sent Harshal Patel back. Full outside off, driven wide of extra-cover where Uthappa dives but misses, Conway from mid-off gets there and by then Harshal is at the other end, but is sent back, has to hare across, the throw is on the bounce to Pretorius who takes one bail off with his hands without the ball but then deflects it onto the other stump and bail which lights up, with Harshal's dive caught just short. The third umpire has a good look and reckons he is fine with Pretorius' effort. Harshal Patel run out (Conway/Pretorius) 0(0)

Commentary Text: Pretorius to Lomror, 2 runs, this is already an expensive over, and 3 more balls to come still. Full outside off, looked to be the seam-up delivery, Lomror slices across the ball and the skier is dropped by the onrushing Jadeja from deep cover. Seems to have injured himnself as his right knee thuds into the ground and he is holding the back of his head as well - the physio is out there. Coming back to the catch, Jadeja sprinted a long way and got there, will be disappointed at not hanging on. Landed heavily on his left shoulder and may well have been slightly concussed due to the blow to his head, but he carrries on even though looks a bit dazed

Commentary Text: Moeen Ali to Kohli, out Bowled!! Oh through the gate. What a class off-spinner's dismissal. This ain't an England v India Test match. Kohli has got out to spin yet again and don't look at the strikerate again please. This pitch has turn. Moeen does bowl a flatter trajectory and get turn. Lured Kohli into a flick, but he played too far across the line. Didn't get to the pitch of the bat, yet tried to shot. Ball sneaked through to hit middle and leg. Dream dismissal for an offie to go through the gate and get a class player out. Kohli b Moeen Ali 30(33) [4s-3 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Jadeja to Kohli, out Maxwell Run Out!! Yes-no and gone! These two have had stuttering starts for a run a few times and the lack of communication has led to Maxi being sold down the river. Kohli stepped out and defended this away-turner towards cover. He took off and then hit the brakes. Maybe Maxwell paused for a wee bit too to casue that confusion, but both released their brakes and skated through. Unfortunately for RCB the throw was spot on from Robbie and MS did the rest to catch Maxi short. Maxwell run out (Uthappa/Dhoni) 3(3)

Commentary Text: Moeen Ali to du Plessis, out Caught by Jadeja!! In the airrr, mistimed, taken at deep mid-wicket. This is MS Dhoni the captain playing with the opposition. There is turn and bounce on this pitch. CSK had just bowled two quiet overs and they also had to cover up for Simarjeet if need be later on. So Dhoni bravely brought on Moeen despite two right-handers at the crease. But he got his offie on to bowl with a big leg-side and invite the big hit. Faf tried to smash this over mid-wicket and holed out on the deep as he met the pull shot high on the bat. du Plessis c Jadeja b Moeen Ali 38(22) [4s-4 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Hasaranga to Conway, out Caught by Shahbaz Ahmed!! He lived by the sweep, he falls to the sweep. Absolutely middled this slog-sweep, but picked out deep backward square leg to perfection. What a brilliant change and RCB get a huge wicket. Often we see teams reluctant to bowl leggie with two lefties in, but Faf rolled the dice and got his man. Was in the slot for Conway, but he hit to the fielder and walks off disappointed after a very good innings. Pressure back on CSK now. Conway c Shahbaz Ahmed b Hasaranga 56(37) [4s-6 6s-2]
